    "decisionConsequence": "Moderate",
    "description": "A finite element model is used to predict relative micromotion at the bone-implant interface of a cementless tibial tray under physiological gait and stair-climb loading. Model influence is MODERATE (model supplements cadaveric bench testing for design optimization); decision consequence is MODERATE (incorrect prediction could lead to suboptimal implant geometry but clinical risk is mitigated by additional bench and animal studies). Model Risk Level 3 per the Nagaraja/Morrison framework.",
